            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EDaniel%20and%20his%20friends%20were%20men%20of%20integrity.%20Captured%20by%20the%20armies%20of%20Nebuchadnezzar%20of%20Babylon%2C%20Daniel%20and%20three%20others%20from%20Judah's%20royal%20family%20were%20ordered%20to%20live%20in%20the%20king's%20palace%20for%20a%20three-year%20training%20period.%20Early%20on%20they%20resolved%20not%20to%20defile%20themselves%20with%20the%20royal%20food%20and%20wine%20offered%20by%20the%20king's%20servants%20(Daniel%201%3A8).%20Everything%20about%20these%20young%20men%20testified%20of%20the%20good%2C%20wholesome%20will%20of%20God%20in%20their%20lives.%20Then%20came%20the%20time%20for%20their%20testing.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20did%20everything%20he%20could%20to%20destroy%20them%20and%20their%20influence%20with%20the%20king.%20It%20seemed%20as%20though%20their%20doom%20was%20sealed%20until%20Daniel%20spoke%20to%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20guard%20with%20%22wisdom%20and%20discretion%22%20(2%3A14).%20His%20wise%20words%20won%20him%20and%20his%20friends%20a%20stay%20of%20execution.%20Later%20that%20night%20the%20Lord%20revealed%20the%20king's%20disturbing%20dream%20to%20Daniel.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20harmed%2C%20Daniel%20and%20his%20friends%20were%20promoted!%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20you%20come%20under%20persecution%2C%20be%20certain%20you%20are%20pursuing%20God's%20good%20will%20with%20all%20your%20heart.%20He%20will%20give%20you%20the%20favor%20you%20need%20with%20whoever%20is%20responsible.%20%22The%20eyes%20of%20the%20Lord%20watch%20over%20those%20who%20do%20right%2C%20and%20his%20ears%20are%20open%20to%20their%20prayers.%20But%20the%20Lord%20turns%20his%20face%20against%20those%20who%20do%20evil%22%20(1%20Peter%203%3A12).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Daniel.1:1-2:23",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EDaniel%201%3A1-2%3A23%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_1%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EDaniel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDaniel%20in%20Nebuchadnezzar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EDuring%20the%20third%20year%20of%20King%20Jehoiakim%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20This%20event%20occurred%20in%20605%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20during%20the%20third%20year%20of%20Jehoiakim%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20(according%20to%20the%20calendar%20system%20in%20which%20the%20new%20year%20begins%20in%20the%20spring).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20of%20Babylon%20came%20to%20Jerusalem%20and%20besieged%20it.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_2%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Lord%20gave%20him%20victory%20over%20King%20Jehoiakim%20of%20Judah%20and%20permitted%20him%20to%20take%20some%20of%20the%20sacred%20objects%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20God.%20So%20Nebuchadnezzar%20took%20them%20back%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Babylonia%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20land%20of%20Shinar.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20placed%20them%20in%20the%20treasure-house%20of%20his%20god.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_3%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20king%20ordered%20Ashpenaz%2C%20his%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20to%20bring%20to%20the%20palace%20some%20of%20the%20young%20men%20of%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20royal%20family%20and%20other%20noble%20families%2C%20who%20had%20been%20brought%20to%20Babylon%20as%20captives.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_4%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BSelect%20only%20strong%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20good-looking%20young%20men%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BMake%20sure%20they%20are%20well%20versed%20in%20every%20branch%20of%20learning%2C%20are%20gifted%20with%20knowledge%20and%20good%20judgment%2C%20and%20are%20suited%20to%20serve%20in%20the%20royal%20palace.%20Train%20these%20young%20men%20in%20the%20language%20and%20literature%20of%20Babylon.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Eof%20the%20Chaldeans.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_5%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20assigned%20them%20a%20daily%20ration%20of%20food%20and%20wine%20from%20his%20own%20kitchens.%20They%20were%20to%20be%20trained%20for%20three%20years%2C%20and%20then%20they%20would%20enter%20the%20royal%20service.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_6%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EDaniel%2C%20Hananiah%2C%20Mishael%2C%20and%20Azariah%20were%20four%20of%20the%20young%20men%20chosen%2C%20all%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_7%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20chief%20of%20staff%20renamed%20them%20with%20these%20Babylonian%20names%3A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22list-sp%22%3EDaniel%20was%20called%20Belteshazzar.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list%22%3EHananiah%20was%20called%20Shadrach.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list%22%3EMishael%20was%20called%20Meshach.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22list%22%3EAzariah%20was%20called%20Abednego.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_8%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Daniel%20was%20determined%20not%20to%20defile%20himself%20by%20eating%20the%20food%20and%20wine%20given%20to%20them%20by%20the%20king.%20He%20asked%20the%20chief%20of%20staff%20for%20permission%20not%20to%20eat%20these%20unacceptable%20foods.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_9%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20God%20had%20given%20the%20chief%20of%20staff%20both%20respect%20and%20affection%20for%20Daniel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_10%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20responded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20afraid%20of%20my%20lord%20the%20king%2C%20who%20has%20ordered%20that%20you%20eat%20this%20food%20and%20wine.%20If%20you%20become%20pale%20and%20thin%20compared%20to%20the%20other%20youths%20your%20age%2C%20I%20am%20afraid%20the%20king%20will%20have%20me%20beheaded.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_11%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EDaniel%20spoke%20with%20the%20attendant%20who%20had%20been%20appointed%20by%20the%20chief%20of%20staff%20to%20look%20after%20Daniel%2C%20Hananiah%2C%20Mishael%2C%20and%20Azariah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_12%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BPlease%20test%20us%20for%20ten%20days%20on%20a%20diet%20of%20vegetables%20and%20water%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Daniel%20said.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_13%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ten%20days%2C%20see%20how%20we%20look%20compared%20to%20the%20other%20young%20men%20who%20are%20eating%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20food.%20Then%20make%20your%20decision%20in%20light%20of%20what%20you%20see.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_14%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20attendant%20agreed%20to%20Daniel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20suggestion%20and%20tested%20them%20for%20ten%20days.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_15%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ten%20days%2C%20Daniel%20and%20his%20three%20friends%20looked%20healthier%20and%20better%20nourished%20than%20the%20young%20men%20who%20had%20been%20eating%20the%20food%20assigned%20by%20the%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_16%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20after%20that%2C%20the%20attendant%20fed%20them%20only%20vegetables%20instead%20of%20the%20food%20and%20wine%20provided%20for%20the%20others.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_17%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EGod%20gave%20these%20four%20young%20men%20an%20unusual%20aptitude%20for%20understanding%20every%20aspect%20of%20literature%20and%20wisdom.%20And%20God%20gave%20Daniel%20the%20special%20ability%20to%20interpret%20the%20meanings%20of%20visions%20and%20dreams.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_18%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20training%20period%20ordered%20by%20the%20king%20was%20completed%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20staff%20brought%20all%20the%20young%20men%20to%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_19%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20talked%20with%20them%2C%20and%20no%20one%20impressed%20him%20as%20much%20as%20Daniel%2C%20Hananiah%2C%20Mishael%2C%20and%20Azariah.%20So%20they%20entered%20the%20royal%20service.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_20%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EWhenever%20the%20king%20consulted%20them%20in%20any%20matter%20requiring%20wisdom%20and%20balanced%20judgment%2C%20he%20found%20them%20ten%20times%20more%20capable%20than%20any%20of%20the%20magicians%20and%20enchanters%20in%20his%20entire%20kingdom.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_1_21%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EDaniel%20remained%20in%20the%20royal%20service%20until%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20reign%20of%20King%20Cyrus.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A21%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Cyrus%20began%20his%20reign%20(over%20Babylon)%20in%20539%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_2_1%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EDaniel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ENebuchadnezzar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Dream%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20night%20during%20the%20second%20year%20of%20his%20reign%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E2%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20second%20year%20of%20Nebuchadnezzar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20was%20603%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Nebuchadnezzar%20had%20such%20disturbing%20dreams%20that%20he%20couldn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20sleep.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_2_2%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20called%20in%20his%20magicians%2C%20enchanters%2C%20sorcerers%2C%20and%20astrologers%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E2%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EChaldeans%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%202%3A4%2C%205%2C%2010.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20he%20demanded%20that%20they%20tell%20him%20what%20he%20had%20dreamed.%20As%20they%20stood%20before%20the%20king%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_2_3%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20had%20a%20dream%20that%20deeply%20troubles%20me%2C%20and%20I%20must%20know%20what%20it%20means.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22dani_2_4%22%20bk%3D%22dani%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20astrologers%20answered%20the%20king%20in%20Aramaic%2C%3Ca%20class%3D